{
  "texts": [
    "To promote structured and localized interactions, we also initialize a learned coordinate grid Ξ for these latent queries.",
    "These coordinates are used to compute attention biases, encouraging stronger attention between spatially adjacent tokens.",
    "The cross-attention module outputs an intermediate field ∈ R |Ξ|×h, which is further refined using Physics Attention (Wu et al., 2024a) to reduce computational overhead.",
    "Geometry-aware encoding As presented in section 3.2, we introduce a geometry-aware attention bias that promotes attention locality.",
    "Section D.1.1 illustrates how this penalization is applied."
  ]
}